AAA.name: Unit net weight
AAA.desc: [6160] Weight (mass) of goods including any packing normally going with them to a buyer in a retail sale.

AAB.name: Unit gross weight
AAB.desc: [6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the carrier's equipment.

AAD.name: Total gross weight
AAD.desc: [6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the carrier's equipment.

AAE.name: Item gross weight
AAE.desc: Gross weight at line item level.

AAF.name: Net net weight
AAF.desc: [6048] Weight (mass) of the goods themselves without any packing.

AAL.name: Net weight
AAL.desc: [6160] Weight (mass) of goods including any packing normally going with them to a buyer in a retail sale.

AAM.name: Gross tonnage of the vessel
AAM.desc: [6300] The measure of the overall size of a ship determined in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969.

AAN.name: Net tonnage of the vessel
AAN.desc: [6302] The measure of the useful capacity of a ship determined in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention on Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969.

AAU.name: Operative temperature
AAU.desc: Temperature identified system or process works according to specifications.

AAV.name: Non operative temperature
AAV.desc: Temperature identified system or process does not work according to specifications.

AAW.name: Gross volume
AAW.desc: The observed volume unadjusted for factors such as temperature or gravity.

AAX.name: Net volume
AAX.desc: The observed volume after adjustment for factors such as temperature or gravity.

ABF.name: Test piece dimensions
ABF.desc: The size of the test piece that was tested.

ABG.name: Average reading
ABG.desc: Average reading of the test being reported on.

ABH.name: External dimension
ABH.desc: The outer measurement of the referenced item or package.

ABI.name: Internal dimension
ABI.desc: The inner measurement of the referenced item or package.

ABJ.name: Volume
ABJ.desc: The amount of air space taken up by the entity identified in the 6311 qualifier.

ABK.name: Loading meter
ABK.desc: A measurement dimension given in loading meters.

ABL.name: Retail container dimension
ABL.desc: Single physical dimension of a retail container.

ABM.name: Retail container size
ABM.desc: Size of a retail container in terms of volume.

ABN.name: Other US Government agency application
ABN.desc: Application of an other US government agency.

ABQ.name: Percentage of alcohol (by volume)
ABQ.desc: The percentage of alcohol contained in a liquid.

ABR.name: Dimensions total weight
ABR.desc: Total weight resulting from the dimensions.

ABU.name: Licence (quantity deducted)
ABU.desc: Quantity to be written off from the total license amount.

ABV.name: Cargo loaded
ABV.desc: Total tonnage of cargo loaded onto the conveyance.

ABW.name: Cargo discharged
ABW.desc: Total tonnage of cargo unloaded from the conveyance.

ABY.name: Conveyance summer dead weight
ABY.desc: Registered summer dead weight total tonnage of the vessel.

ABZ.name: Containerized cargo on vessel's weight
ABZ.desc: Total weight of containerized cargo on vessel.

ACA.name: Non-containerized cargo on vessel's weight
ACA.desc: Total weight of non-containerized cargo on vessel.

ACB.name: 1st specified tariff quantity
ACB.desc: Primary reportable quantity associated with a tariff number.

ACC.name: 2nd specified tariff quantity
ACC.desc: Secondary reportable quantity associated with a tariff number.

ACD.name: 3rd specified tariff quantity
ACD.desc: Third reportable quantity associated with a tariff number.

ACE.name: Weight ascertained
ACE.desc: [4240] Endorsement of the true weight (mass) as ascertained or verified by the railway (CIM 81).

ACF.name: Chemistry
ACF.desc: Measurement related to a chemical measurement system.

ACG.name: Chargeable weight
ACG.desc: The weight on which charges are based.

ACI.name: Core size
ACI.desc: A measurement indicating the core size of an object.

ACJ.name: Decision result value
ACJ.desc: A measurement in relation to value representing a decision result.

ACK.name: Dimensional tolerance
ACK.desc: Tolerance in relation to a dimension.

ACM.name: Dimension used in price extension
ACM.desc: Dimension used in relation to a price.

ACN.name: Estimated gross weight
ACN.desc: Estimated weight (mass) of goods, including packing and excluding carrier's.

ACO.name: Environmental conditions
ACO.desc: The data values to be reported reflect the environmental conditions surrounding a situation including but not limited to test environments.

ACP.name: Estimated volume
ACP.desc: Estimated size or measure of anything in three dimensions.

ACR.name: Interpolated value
ACR.desc: A value interpolated from a number of values.

ACS.name: Vessel overall length
ACS.desc: Total overall length of the vessel.

ACT.name: Limited coil measurement
ACT.desc: Value limiting the measurement of a coil.

ACU.name: Lift limitation
ACU.desc: A measurement indicating the lift capacity limitation.

ACV.name: Loading meters
ACV.desc: The length in a vehicle, whereby the complete width and height over that length is needed for the goods.

ACW.name: Number of axles
ACW.desc: Number of axles of movable equipment or means of transport on wheels.

ACX.name: Payload
ACX.desc: The revenue-producing load carried by a means of transport.

ACY.name: Parting cut (sawcut)
ACY.desc: A measurement related to the cutting of items.

ACZ.name: Physical dimensions
ACZ.desc: A measurement indicating the physical dimensions of an object.

ADA.name: Package limitations
ADA.desc: A measurement indicating limitation associated with packages.

ADB.name: Platform limitation
ADB.desc: A measurement indicating limitation in relation to a platform.

ADC.name: Receiving facility limitations
ADC.desc: A measurement indicating limitations in relation to a receiving facility.

ADD.name: Property specification
ADD.desc: Indicates that the data to follow are target specifications.

ADE.name: Shipping tolerance
ADE.desc: A measurement indicating a tolerance in relation to the transport.

ADF.name: Shade
ADF.desc: A measurement in relation to the shade.

ADG.name: Storage limitation
ADG.desc: A measurement indicating limitation in relation to storage.

ADI.name: Surface treatment
ADI.desc: A measurement in relation to surface treatment.

ADJ.name: Surface
ADJ.desc: A measurement in relation a surface.

ADK.name: Specification value
ADK.desc: A measurable item characteristic specified by the buyer, seller or third party.

ADL.name: Transportation equipment limitations
ADL.desc: A measurement indicating limitations in relation to transport equipment.

ADM.name: Test result
ADM.desc: Indicates that the data to follow is the test result measurements.

ADN.name: Time used in price extension
ADN.desc: Time value in relation to a price.

ADO.name: Observed value
ADO.desc: The reported test result which includes measurement variability.

ADP.name: True value
ADP.desc: The reported test result with the measurement variability removed.

ADQ.name: Weight used in price extension
ADQ.desc: A weight measurement in relation to a price.

ADR.name: Start position in the length
ADR.desc: The starting position from the beginning of an item located in the length direction.

ADS.name: End position in the length
ADS.desc: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the length direction.

ADT.name: Start position in the width
ADT.desc: The start position from the beginning of an item located in the width direction.

ADU.name: End position in the width
ADU.desc: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the width direction.

ADV.name: Start position in the thickness
ADV.desc: The start position from the beginning of an item located in the thickness direction.

ADW.name: End position in the thickness
ADW.desc: The end position from the beginning of an item located in the thickness direction.

CT.name: Contents of package
CT.desc: In combination with the other data elements of the actual segment this code indicates the measured content of a package.

CV.name: Commercial weight
CV.desc: Item weight considering its maximum possible humidity.

CZ.name: Core length
CZ.desc: To specify length of core (of spod/babbin etc.) on which product is to be placed.

D.name: Destination weight agreement
D.desc: The agreed weight of despatched goods whose weight may change during transport.

FI.name: Filament count
FI.desc: Used e.g. in textile, print industries.

G.name: Gross weight
G.desc: [6292] Weight (mass) of goods including packing but excluding the carrier's equipment.

LN.name: Length dimension
LN.desc: (6168) Length of pieces or packages stated for transport purposes.

MO.name: Moisture
MO.desc: Measurement application is the moisture content of the item.

RJ.name: Rockwell C
RJ.desc: Hardness in the Rockwell C scale.

TC.name: Temperature
TC.desc: A measurement in relation to temperature.

XH.name: Side height, flat bed with removable sides
